Connecting to MongoDB using PyMongo¶

To connect to MongoDB and work with data using Python, we will be installing Pymongo driver.

The easiest way to install the driver is through the pip package management system. Execute the following on a command line or Anaconda Prompt :

Command line:
python -m pip install pymongo

Anaconda Prompt:

pip install pymongo

pip3 install 'pymongo[srv]'

In [ ]:
! pip install pymongo  # ad
! pip3 install 'pymongo[srv]'

ERROR: Invalid requirement: '#'

[notice] A new release of pip is available: 23.2.1 -> 24.0
[notice] To update, run: python.exe -m pip install --upgrade pip

[notice] A new release of pip is available: 23.2.1 -> 24.0

Once PyMongo is installed we can write our first application that will return information about the MongoDB server. In your Python development environment or from a text editor enter the following code.

In [ ]:
#ad
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')
In [ ]:
#ad
import pymongo # ad
from pprint import pprint
# connect to MongoDB, change the << MONGODB URL >> to reflect your own connection string
client = pymongo.MongoClient("mongodb+srv://avulli:root@cluster0.hnq2erb.mongodb.net/")

Exploring Collections and Documents¶

A collection in MongoDB is a container for documents. A database is the container for collections. Some of the advantages of storing data in documents are dynamic & flexible schema and the ability to store arrays can be seen from our simple Python scripts.

# need to change the column names to remove spaces
inventory.columns = inventory.columns.str.replace(' ', '_')
# need to change the column name patient_number to Patient_Number
inventory.rename(columns = {'practicezip9code':'zip_code'}, inplace = True)
inventory.rename(columns = {'practiceaddress1':'address1'}, inplace = True)
inventory.rename(columns = {'practicecity':'city'}, inplace = True)
inventory.rename(columns = {'practicestate':'state'}, inplace = True)
inventory.rename(columns = {'Delivery_time_(days)':'days_in_store'}, inplace = True)

# modifying the date colum to be date data type

inventory['Date_Purchased'] = pd.to_datetime(inventory['Date_Purchased'])

  3. multiple values joined by OR

Bar Chart of Supply Quantity by Type:¶

In [ ]:
#sdb
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

pipeline_supply_quantity = [
    {"$group": {"_id": "$supplieslist", "total_quantity": {"$sum": "$Quantity"}}}
]

supply_quantity_result = db.aggregate(pipeline_supply_quantity)

supply_types = []
total_quantities = []

for result in supply_quantity_result:
    supply_types.append(result['_id'])
    total_quantities.append(result['total_quantity'])

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.bar(supply_types, total_quantities, color='skyblue')
plt.xlabel('Supply Type')
plt.ylabel('Total Quantity')
plt.title('Total Quantity of Each Medical Supply Type')
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Pie Chart of Supply Distribution by Category:¶

In [ ]:
#sdb
pipeline_supply_category = [
    {"$group": {"_id": "$supplieslist", "count": {"$sum": 1}}}
]

supply_category_result = db.aggregate(pipeline_supply_category)

labels = []
counts = []

for result in supply_category_result:
    labels.append(result['_id'])
    counts.append(result['count'])

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))
plt.pie(counts, labels=labels, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=140)
plt.title('Distribution of Medical Supplies by Category')
plt.axis('equal')
plt.show()

Line Chart of Epoetin Quantity Over Time:¶

In [ ]:
#sdb

supply_name = "Epoetin"

pipeline_supply_quantity_over_time = [
    {"$match": {"supplieslist": supply_name}},
    {"$group": {"_id": {"$dateToString": {"format": "%Y-%m-%d", "date": "$Date_Purchased"}}, "total_quantity": {"$sum": "$Quantity"}}},
    {"$sort": {"_id": 1}}
]

supply_quantity_over_time_result = db.aggregate(pipeline_supply_quantity_over_time)

dates = []
quantities = []

for result in supply_quantity_over_time_result:
    dates.append(result['_id'])
    quantities.append(result['total_quantity'])

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(dates, quantities, marker='o', color='green', linestyle='-')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Total Quantity')
plt.title('Quantity of {} Over Time'.format(supply_name))
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

Histogram of Infusion Drug Prices¶

In [ ]:
#nr

supply_name = "Infusion Drugs"

pipeline_supply_prices = [
    {"$match": {"supplieslist": supply_name}},
    {"$group": {"_id": None, "prices": {"$push": "$Unit_Price"}}}
]

supply_prices_result = db.aggregate(pipeline_supply_prices)
for result in supply_prices_result:
    prices = result['prices']

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.hist(prices, bins=20, color='skyblue', edgecolor='black')
plt.xlabel('Price')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.title('Distribution of Prices for {}'.format(supply_name))
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
